name: Generate Prime Numbers
desc: Implementation of Odd Sieve of Erasthotones optimized to work partitioned that will generate all primes that are in the first 10000000 numbers.
kernel: var from=params.data[0];var to=params.data[1];var memorySize=((to-from+1)/2)|0;var isPrime=[];for(var i=0;i<memorySize;i++){isPrime[i]=1}for(var i=3;i*i<=to;i+=2){if(i>=3*3&&i%3==0)continue;if(i>=5*5&&i%5==0)continue;if(i>=7*7&&i%7==0)continue;if(i>=11*11&&i%11==0)continue;if(i>=13*13&&i%13==0)continue;var minJ=((((from+i-1)/i)|0)*i);if(minJ<i*i){minJ=i*i}if((minJ&1)==0){minJ+=i}for(var j=minJ;j<=to;j+=2*i){var index=((j-from)/2)|0;isPrime[index]=0}}var found=[];if(from<=2){found.push(2)}var pos=from+1;for(var i=0;i<memorySize;i++){if(isPrime[i]==1){found.push(pos)}pos+=2}delete isPrime;result=found;
